European Stocks Drop for Second Day Amid Concern Portugal May Need Bailout

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-03-23T08:02:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/european-stocks-drop-for-second-day-amid-concern-portugal-may-need-bailout.html
European stocks fell for a second
day amid concern that  Portugal  may be forced to seek a bailout
as it struggles to trim debt and implement the deepest spending
cuts in more than three decades.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index slipped 0.3 percent to 271.12 at
8:01 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  